##From fitness instructor to delivery man

Micro signal

Function description, we are with you in this battle

By Yang chang-an

The day after Valentine's Day, Xinye began to help people who could not return to Wuhan from other places to feed their pets.
Before that, the fitness instructor had delivered food and supplies to residents of Wuhan who could not go out for nine days with only a cotton mask. It was also chilly in Wuhan in February, when Xinye, registered as a temporary errand boy, caught a cold after days of cycling and delivering goods.
After resting at home for a while and making sure he was feeling well, Sino resumed helping others.
Here's what Sino says:
On January 23rd, I woke up to the news that the city was closed, and found that all my friends were fighting for food. I thought I'd get something to eat, even if I wasn't robbing the produce. Then I went to the supermarket to buy two packets of instant noodles, saw a lot of shops selling masks, I want not to buy some masks. But then I realized I didn't need it, so I went home.
I didn't know anything about the outbreak at the time, and I didn't know anything about the siege. Originally thought that the city just can not take transport, the door or can go out, including the city a day or two after I went out feeling wearing masks is not much. But then the numbers came out, and I knew it had gotten this bad.
The idea of running errands, because one day in the group to see a lot of people say that can not go out, can not buy food, or the family's children are almost not to eat milk powder, take-out boy and shortage of manpower, the order can be met by luck.
I looked at the heart very sad, and decided to make a contribution to the people of Wuhan. My Body is good immunity is strong, may deliver the necessaries of life to the people who can not go out.

We can't let them starve, can we?
My family is in Inner Mongolia and I have no intention of telling them about my errands. I was prepared for this, so even though I couldn't buy a mask, didn't have a suit, didn't have goggles, I made it to size 10.
On average, I get about five orders a day, each of which costs about $20 or $10. I buy food four or five single buy, prepare food, queue, pay the bill to take almost five hours, will take two hours to send the bill, until 6 pm Electric car power I will go home. Almost any order will run out of time because it will take a long time just to grab the food and wait in line, but the customer will understand.

It's from Shinye's errands

The first few days of looting food situation is quite serious, after a bit of ease up.

Supermarkets are currently relatively short of staple food goods, such as noodles, instant noodles, flour, dumplings and so on, meat, Ham sausage is also more difficult to buy, vegetables supply is OK. Recently, because we do not go out for a while, on rice, flour, soy sauce, salt, fruit demand up, the order also to Sanitary Napkins.

Once I was delivering food to an isolated family, and my bike ran out of power, so I rode my bike-share. That day, I put a bag in the basket of my bike. Each of the two faucets was hung with a bag. It was very heavy, so I rode slowly.

The guest insisted that I leave it at the gate of the community, and he would come down later to pick it up. Later, I learned that their home is being quarantined, so he could not meet with me, had to thank in Wechat.

Another time, I received a Douban friends to help with food delivery. I rode a shared bike 80 kilometers from Guanggu in the Far East to Houhu in the far west. I didn't charge a penny for running errands.

Xinye delivers vegetables on his bicycle

When I recorded the experience on Weibo, some netizens questioned whether I had sent the order for money. Actually, I wouldn't do it for the money, because I wasn't running errands during the epidemic. I often saw on the platform to be sent from Wuchang to Hankou, that is to cross the river of the single, there are more than 100 dollars to run errands, but I never took.

I just felt able to help this person, so I went.

A lot of people talk on their mobile phones and don't do anything, but question the people who do it. Why I do not feel very depressed now, because I am giving warmth to others every day, others are also giving back to me warmth.

Every day when I run alone, I have no time to eat, drink, or go to the bathroom. I'm not an outdoor worker myself. My work and life are mostly indoors, so I don't have very thick clothes. Cycling is often very cold, and sometimes it's even colder with a light rain.

At the beginning of some places not familiar with the road, but also a hand control car, a hand holding a cell phone to see the location of the guests. One day my car ran out of electricity, in the middle of the night to go back to the cart ten kilometers, there is no one on the road.

Night in Wuhan

At the time I wondered why I did it, but then I realized that if I saw someone else with one less problem in their life, I'd be happy.

I didn't want to give up when I was sick. I think that whatever you do is like a workout, and if you need a reason to do it, it's easy to give it up. So at the beginning to do this thing I did not struggle, and in the end I will not give up for any reason.

My opinion is that there is no need to worry too much about the death of a well-built old man reported by the media some time ago. Fitness doesn't equal health, and muscle mass doesn't equal a strong immune system. Health and good living habits, as well as taking precautions during an outbreak, have nothing to do with whether or not you have muscles.

From the beginning unknown delivery, to later in Douban, Weibo attention, I think the biggest change in their mentality is to find this society is too much in need of love. After connecting with so many strangers and receiving so much care from all over the world, I feel that we are all capable of giving love.

My wechat signature is "welcome to the world" , which means I feel that the world is warm and worthwhile, and I hope you can warm the world with me.

I will continue to run errands to Kaesong, accompanied by the city towards the new life.
